\vec{r}(t):=\sin(t)\vec{i}+[\cos(t)+\ln[\tan(t/2)]]\vec{j}
t\in(0,\pi)
dy/dx
x=f(t)=\sin(t)
y=g(t)=\cos(t)+\ln[\tan(t/2)]
T = \left|\dfrac{y}{y'}\sqrt{y'^2+1}\right|
